messages.text:
There was a 5mm error in the board-height parameter LA has been using. Alenni is now aware of it and said she will get LA to fix it in future solves. 

Hopefully these two fixes will resolve the manual correction step.
That’s awesome. Sorry about the mislead.
Great. I will also make sure LA is setting the 'board height' parameter correctly.

Hey, Pro. I think I was wrong. 
I have the grid floor in web director offset slightly so it would render over any background/floor textures. 
It was set to 0.01 cm and I think I failed to convert that into meters when we updated the units used in web director.
Which means it would actually be rendering the grid 10mm higher than ground, and explain why Lucas needs to locate the assets below the grid.
